# Clean Architecture Refactor Guardrails

- Prefer extracting pure helpers first, then side-effect orchestration, then UI composition. Add or update focused tests before moving behavior that is not purely mechanical.
- Keep React components declarative: UI components should receive commands/state through props or hooks, and browser/runtime operations should live in action/service modules.
- Keep the markdown article DOM boundary intact: `renderDocument()` -> `sanitizeHtml()` -> `renderIntoElement()` remains the only normal path to set rendered markdown HTML.
- Keep MV3 browser APIs in ownership layers: background services for `chrome.*` background work, messaging helpers for UI/content callers, viewer action modules for document commands.
- Avoid growing files beyond roughly 300 lines unless there is a strong reason. When a file crosses that size, look for independent responsibilities before adding more logic.
- When splitting modules, update `docs/project-overview-for-ai.md` and any affected lifecycle rules in the same change or in the next documentation-only change.
- Refactor one boundary at a time. Do not combine UI redesign, behavior change, and file movement in the same patch unless the behavior change is required by the extraction.
